inn1.comm: loosener, angled across the stumps with not enough carry to Dhoni, back with the gloves again, left alone by van Wyk
short of a length on leg stump, its turned to square leg and de Villiers has to turn and hustle back to his end after setting off down the pitch
that was close! Pitches on a length and comes in, van Wyk decides to leave it and it clips him high on the thigh and just misses clipping the top of off
a touch fuller, 129ks, left alone and again the ball doesnt carry well to Dhoni
overpitched and its driven to mid-off, too much bottom hand on the shot
good length on the stumps, he gets forward and then has to check the shot back down the track
drifts onto leg stump, de Villiers mistimes the shot off the pads to square leg and declines the run
back of a length and straightening, he gets caught in the crease as he defends it well outside the line of off stump
back of a length, good channel outside off stump, left alone
good length, fuller than the last ball and it comes in, de Villiers defending and getting an inside-edge to Chawla at square leg
good stuff, pitching on a good length, straightening again, and beating a tame forward drive, how close was that to missing the edge?
back of a length, no room on offer, de Villiers gets behind it and defends
good length on the stumps, van Wyk wants to work it to leg but adjusts to defend it back to Zaheer
good ball, pitching on an almost unplayable length and swinging late, deveating past van Wyk's bat after he decided to play at it
another good ball, no room at all and van Wyk defends it back down the pitch
beaten, van Wyk confused by the late movement, just feeling for it off the front foot and missing
back of a length just outside off stump, straightens and van Wyk gets behind the line
pitches out a short length outside off stump and swings away, van Wyk leaves it be
first runs come courtesy a shocker of a wide outside leg stump, swinging away and Dhoni's dive parries it off for a single

madness! Short of a length on leg stump, van Wyk works it to square leg, no one's there and de Villiers calls for the run, RP does the fielding himself and van Wyk sends his partner back, bowler fires in a throw back to Dravid, who disturbs the bails but replays show de Villiers' bat was just in the air after he dived full stretch
back of a length,  pitches outside leg stump and catches him on the hop
back of a length on middle and leg, van Wyk gets behind the ball and defends back to RP
pitches on a good length and swings away, van Wyk gets the front leg forward and leaves it pretty close to off stump
short and wide, he cuts hard but cant beat Yuvraj, diving to his right from backward point
good length, no room to drive, van Wyk plays it back to RP Singh
good delivery, pitching on a length and straightening, he leaves it be and the ball comes in off a length
first runs off the bat, Kallis defending forward and getting an inside-edge to backward square leg
good length, van Wyk gets forward and punches back past mid-off for his first runs
good length delivery, Zaheer looking for movement, Kallis gets the leg forward and shoulders arms
back of a length outside off stump, Kallis defends with an open face and picks up one through the vacant gully region
back of a length, van Wyk gets behind it and defends to point
short of a length on middle stump, comes in sharply with good bounce, catching Kallis in the midriff as he hops up

bowled  'em! RP follows up the short delivery with one fuller outside off stump and Kallis defends with a good gap between bat and pad, the ball coming in off the inside-edge to disturb off stump, and thats the biggest wicket of them all as far as India are concerned
a touch too full outside off stump, Gibbs gets forward and counters the swing with a confident push through cover and point for four

great delivery, pitching back of a length on middle and off, coming in with good bounce and catching Gibbs' front pad, though very high on the roll, and sailing over the stumps, and the appeal is turned down
straighter delivery, Gibbs gets up and defends to square leg
good length outside off stump, gets great carry to Dhoni as Gibbs leaves it be
good length outside off stump, just asking him to come forward and play at it, but van Wyk wisely leaves it alone, excellent line and length from Zaheer
this time he chases one that pitches marginally fuller and goes the other way, and gets beaten on the move
back of a length on off stump, he gets well behind the line and defends off the back foot
now he offers some room, not a lot mind you, but thats a terrific back-foot cut through the covers from van Wyk, good roll of the wrists
good length again, asking him to chase this one too, but van Wyk shoulders arms
pitches outside leg stump and it clips the pad as van Wyk looks to work it fine
full delivery pitches outside leg stump and swings away, good stop from Dhoni
back of a length outside off stump, he gets across and defends to point
full on off stump, a touch slower, driven to mid-on
short of a length, carrying on across Gibbs, who gets up and leaves it alone
full on leg stump, he shuffles and flicks it in the air close to Chawla at midwicket, but landing safely
slower delivery, on a good length, Gibbs gets forward tentatively and defends to cover
back of a length on off stump, Gibbs gets up and defends it back to RP
back of a length, pitching outside leg and moving in, catching him high on the knee roll as he gets back in the crease
fuller and van Wyk gets forward, controlling it down to point
fullish again, he gets forward and drives to cover
short of a length, allowing him room to free the arms and cut, he gets a top-edge that flies over the vacant gully region and down to third man
good length, pitching and moving away and Gibbs, who wanted to drive, holds the bat back at the nth second
good ball again, seaming off the surface and Gibbs, getting forward, has to again withdraw on the shot
good length on the stumps, he comes forward and defends to cover
fuller outside off stump, van Wyk drives loosely off the front foot, with a lot of bottom hand, and he gets an inside-edge onto the pad
bit of room on offer, just like he wants, and he gets up on the back foot and cuts down into the ground in front of point
and again, van Wyk gets the chance to cut down into the ground, this time to other side of point
short of a length outside leg stump, he looks to flick but ends up with a leg bye
good length, straightforward delivery, Gibbs gets onto the front foot and defends to cover
a touch full, pitching and carrying down leg stump, catching him on the leg outside the line
good delivery,  pitching on a good length and coming in, he gets forward and defends with an inside-edge
fuller this time outside off stump, and Gibbs drives hard and misses
full again, coming in from outside off stump and Gibbs defends with a good stride ine
full on off stump, and thats a fine on-drive back down the ground for four
full again, he comes forward and defends to mid-on
full down leg stump, he swings and misses
short on the stumps, he pulls over midwicket and gets four
good length, he comes forward and defends to point
good length delivery on middle and leg, Gibbs gets forward and looks to jab at it, inside-edge onto the pads
good ball, yorker outside leg stump, he looks to flick but gets a leg bye to off
touch short of good length delivery, slanting in, Gibbs stands tall and punches it to cover
fuller length delivery, slanting into the right hander, Gibbs comes on the frontfoot and looks to go for the drive, inside edge onto the pads
short and wide, and he pulls it through midwicket
oversteps, ball is full and Gibbs pushes to covers
good length outside off stump, he comes forward and defends
back of a length, pushed to covers, cant beat the gap
short on the stumps, he pulls into the ground in front of square leg
good length on the stumps, slow ball, defended tentatively off the front foot
short down leg stump, he flicks off the hips and Sharma fields down at fine leg
gone! Short and wide, rank long-hop, but Gibbs just gets back and cracks that off the back foot to Karthik at cover, who holds a neat catch
good ball to get first up, pitching short of a length and lifting, beating his back-foot defensive
short of a length outside off stump again, left alone this time
short of a length on middle stump, he hops and turns it to square leg
back of a length, angled across off stump and he leaves it be
fuller on off stump, he gets across and drives back to the bowler
back of a length, he stands and looks to crash it away, but ends up chopping to point
good length on leg stump, he rolls the wrists and gets one to fine leg
full on leg stump, flicked well but straight to square leg
full outside off stump, comes forward and drives to cover
good length outside off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off stump, Duminy tries to cut, then plays across the line, the oddest shot i've seen in ages, and he gets a flying edge over the slips
slower ball outside leg stump, played to midwicket
back of a length, moving away from off stump, van Wyk plays it and manages to keep it down along the ground out to third man
short of a length on the stumps, Duminy shuffles across and tries to work it off the hips, the ball drops at his feet and rolls close to leg stump
full outside off stump, he shuffles across and drives to cover, where Dravid misfields
tossed up on the stumps, Duminy defends to midwicket
well flighted on leg stump, allowing Duminy to sweep with the spin for one
short outside off stump, he gets up and cuts to cover
flatter one on the stumps, he shuffles across and as the ball stays low, he adjusts to pull out to deep backward square leg
well tossed up out the back of the hand, pitching outside off stump and beating hs back-foot defensive
flighted on leg stump, he shuffles and works it to square leg
short  outside leg stump, Duminy gets up and swivels it through backward square out to Powar moving around from fine leg
short of a length outside off stump, he gets up on the toes and defends
back of a length, again he gets behind it and defends to short extra cover
slower ball, pitching outside leg stump, Duminy tries to work it away but the ball sits up on him
short of a length outside leg stump again, and he tucks it out past square leg with ease
good length outside off stump, dabbed with soft hands wide of point for one
tossed up, its full, van Wyk doesnt read it and goes back, then it spins past his back-foot cut
a little to full and he drives it back to Chawla
tossed up slowly, bringing him forward in defense
good shot, van Wyk using the feet well, making it into a full toss and hammering it over long-on for half a dozen
slow delivery, on a length, he gets back and drives to cover
tossed up down leg stump, Duminy gets down and sweeps but cant beat short fine leg
too short and wide, allowing van Wyk to cut to the right of point and out to Powar
good length outside off stump, steered to Yuvraj at point
fuller this time, and Duminy doesnt let it go, producing a flowing straight-drive past mid-off
fuller again, a touch wider, he drives hard and gets a thick-edge along the ground to third man
good length outside off stump, he gets a good look at it and leaves it be
full outside off stump, van Wyk drives and misses all ends up
tossed up on off stump, he comes forward and defends
tossed up again, this time he sweeps hard and picks up one to fine leg
tossed up outside off stump, he prods forward, getting well across, and takes it on the front leg
tossed up again, he comes out and again prods forward
quicker and flatter outside leg stump, van Wyk flicks out to Tendulkar at square leg
spins away this time from off stump, Duminy getting behind the line and defending
back of a length outside off stump, he gets back and defends to cover
good length outside off stump, he gets a huge stride forward and the ball clips his leg as he shuffles
short and wide, van Wyk cuts hard through gully out to a robust Powar moving across from third man...he'll probably be bowling very soon
bouncer outside off stump, he tries to pull but misses, and a good take from Dhoni
another bouncer, this time over leg stump, forcing Duminy to duck down
back of a length outside off stump, he gets behind it and defends
back of a length on leg stump, whipped away to deep backward square leg
tossed up on leg stump, he comes out nicely and flicks to midwicket for one
flatter on a length, spins away and he gets back and pulls across the line, timing it grossly and the ball just pops up and drops in front of mid-on
tossed up, he comes out and drives to cover
this one pitches and doesn turn, van Wyk gets back and cuts, beaten by the lack of movement
again, he gets back and tries to cut a flipper this time, and misses
tossed up, he gets a good stride in and opens the face of the bat, running it down to third man
overpitched outside off stump, he stands and drives through the covers nicely, opening the face of the bat, and Tendulkar gives chase and hauls it in
too much width, just where van Wyk likes 'em, and he cuts hard through the covers for four, good shot
again, too short and van Wyk rocks back on the pull, going to 41 with a thump through midwicket
good length outside off stump, where he should be bowling, not allowing him any room and van Wyk gets forward and defends towards point
short of a length, van Wyk steps across to outside off stump and works it into midwicket for one
another short ball outside leg stump, Duminy pulls, not in control of the shot, but gets one into the vacant short fine leg area
flat outside leg stump, the wrong un, which Duminy looks to sweep but misses, they all go up in appeal but Billy Bowden isnt interested
flat outside leg stump, swept but to short fine leg
flat down leg stump, nudged into the on side for one
short on leg stump, he pulls into the ground and past the fielder, the ball heads towards fine leg but Tendulkar shows off his boot skills and saves two
tossed up outside off stump, he gets a good look at it and leaves it be
tossed up on leg stump, van Wyk sweeps past square leg
tossed up on middle and leg, nudged to square leg
tossed up outside off stump, it dips but van Wyk sweeps well for one
quicker one, shortish too, Duminy gets across to off and defends it back
tossed up on a length outside off stump, defended to point
tossed up on around leg stump, getting it to spin across the stumps, Duminy defends off the back foot
tossed up outside leg stump, he gets down and tries to sweep but misses out
flat on middle and leg, he gets forward and works it to square leg
spins outside off stump, he cuts out to deep cover and thats the 50-run stand, good effort
comes out, Chawla sees him and floats it up outside leg stump, forcing Duminy to work it to midwicket
tossed up outside off stump, getting him forward on the drive, and cover fields
spins outside off stump, van Wyk gets up and cuts backward of point for one
tossed up wide of off stump, in a flash he backs away to leg and cuts, getting an inside-edge that beats Dhoni and slip and runs away for four
good ball, tossed up outside off stump and dipping, but van Wyk's equally good, pushing with soft hands into covers for one
tossed up outside leg stump, he sweeps once again but fails to make contact, the ball running off the pads for leg-byes
tossed up, straighter delivery, which he defends off the back foot
tossed up, he gets a good stride across and sweeps, but the ball bobs up into his grill
flatter one outside off stump, he gets back and defends
flatter one on the stumps, he steps down the track and drives to Powar's right, the bowler dives and misfields, the ball runs to mid-on and van Wyk has to turn and hurry back to his box
flighted outside leg stump, he steps out and almost gets beaten in the flight, then manages to tuck it to backward square leg
flat outside off stump, giving him room to cut out to deep point and raise his second ODI fifty in three games in Ireland, well played
tossed up on leg stump, worked to square leg for one
well tossed up, he comes down the track and takes it on the pad
flat on leg stump, van Wyk swivels and pulls along the ground out to Tendulkar at backward square leg
tossed up, driven back down the ground, well fielded
tossed up, he uses the feet well and drives in the air to mid-off, but the ball doesnt carry to RP Singh
flat outside off stump, he waits for it and then places it through mid-on off the back foot
nice use of the feet from Duminy, collecting it on the full and driving past mid-off for four
tossed up outside leg stump, he taps it around the corner, runs hard, gets complimented by his partner, and South Africa have three more to the scoreboard
tossed up full on leg stump, he gets down and sweeps, misses, they all appeal but umpire Benson signals leg byes, very close shout
tossed up outside leg stump, he sweeps and misses, not for the first time, and the ball rolls to the off side
seam up, slow medium stuff, a hint of outswing, but van Wyk cuts the short ball out to deep cover
tossed up ever so gently, Duminy gets onto the front foot and drives to mid-off for one
seam-up gets all wrong, just too wide outside leg stump
rank short delivery outside off stump, and van Wyk rightfully clubs that over midwicket for four, aggressive shot
good length on the stumps, he gets forward and flicks into midwicket
slow little dobbler outside off stump, Duminy gets back and opens the face, steering it down to third man for one
tossed up this time outside off stump, too short, and van Wyk pulls out to deep square leg to keep strike
tossed up on off stump, he comes across and flicks in the air in front of square leg
tossed up on leg stump, defended to midwicket
tossed up outside leg stump, flicked to square leg
tossed up well outside leg stump, beating Duminy on the sweep again
a touch quicker outside off stump, no turn, Duminy gets forward and drives to mid-off for one
flat on the stumps, he shuffles and works it to the leg side fielder
tossed up from over the stumps, flat on leg stump, Duminy gets forward and paddles it away for two
tossed up one leg stump, he uses the feet and clips straight to square leg

there's the big breakthrough! Not a good ball at all, very short outside off stump but Duminy chases it, slashing in the air and Dravid, at a sort of short third man, only has to cup his hands above his head and take it easily
tossed up outside off stump, he comes out and drives to cover
tossed up on off stump, he plays across the line and gets off the mark with a quick single to midwicket
tossed up, he strides across the stumps and tries the paddle, but the ball just rolls away in the gap
flat outside off stump, he mistimes the stroke back towards Tendulkar

comes out this time, driving to mid-off and then lazily ambling down the track, then he realizes its a bad call and springts, the fielder fires in a good throw onto the stumps but replays show that van Wyk just made it
tossed up outside off stump, Boucher whips it across the line to midwicket
tossed up, he comes out and drives, mistiming it as he closes the face of the bat, and the ball balloons up between cover and mid-off
tossed up on middle and leg, turned to square leg
tossed up, he dances down and drives over mid-on but Sharma is down near the ropes
flat outside off stump, he comes forward and defends
tossed up, goes the other was as Boucher lunges forward and plays across the line, Dhoni whips off the bails
tossed up, he leaves it alone
tossed up closer to off stump, again Boucher leaves it
flatter delivery, he gets onto the back foot and drives to cover
tossed up down leg stump, he gets down and flicks for one
tossed up well, he gets across and flicks to square leg, Karthik dives around from midwicket and saves runs
flatter on leg stump, worked to short fine leg for one more
moves around the stumps, tosses it up outside leg stump, Boucher plays and misses but the appeal is turned down
tossed up, Boucher dances down, hitting over the top, Sharma at wide long-on fails to judge it, letting it go over him and then as he backtracks he beats the ball to the ropes
tossed up on middle and leg, he stands and works it fine for one
tossed up, it spins across the stumps, and van Wyk stands and drives, a loose shot to get beaten
flat outside off stump, wide too, he cuts but cant beat point
tossed up on middle and leg, he shuffles but cant beat square leg this time
quicker one outside off stump, he stands and tries to cut, cramped for room, and misses
spins outside off stump, he makes room and at the last second drops the hands, running it towards third man, neatly done
tossed up outside off stump, he backs away and cuts hard out past point to bring up the 150
tossed up on leg stump, and he tucks it to midwicket
flat on the stumps, he tries to work it to square leg but mistimes the shot back to Powar
comes out of the crease and drives a tossed-up delivery to mid-off for a quick single
tossed up on leg stump, Boucher flicks to deep backward square leg
tossed up on leg stump, he sweeps in the air behind square and the ball drops well before Yuvraj
tossed up on leg stump, he tucks it to midwicket and sets off, its a tight call for a run and a wide throw from Karthik back to Dhoni lets them off
tossed up outside off stump, he comes onto the front foot and drives to mid-off
tossed up on leg stump, easily pushed into the gap as Yuvraj fields himself
tossed up well outside off stump, the loose ball is cut hard for one
short and wide again, he cuts but cant beat backward point
tossed up, he gets forward and drives hard to Karthik at extra cover
tossed up outside off stump, he gets a good step in and plays, misses, and the appeal is turned down
flat on off stump, driven off the back foot towards Powar at deep midwicket and they run two
tossed up, he flicks across the front pad well wide of short fine leg and Ganguly in the deep does the fielding
tossed up from around the stumps, he uses the feet and hammers it through mid-off for four, shot!
too much air on that one, allowing him the chance to get the front foot out and sweep fine for one
flatter delivery, on a good length, and Boucher defends to cover
tossed up, he gets a stride in and tries that flick again, but closes the face too early and gets a leading-edge to cover for one
tossed up on middle and leg, easily worked into midwicket for one
tossed up, lifts too as he plays and misses
tossed up, quicker delivery, he stands and looks to run it fine, chopping just wide of Dhoni
short and a touch wide, he backs away on the cut but cant beat point
tossed up down leg, he turns it off the pad but Dhoni is quick to field it
flat, arm ball, stays low but he manages to steer it to point
edged and gone! Yuvraj tosses up the arm ball, it stays low as van Wyk makes room and cuts, and the thinnest of under-edges is well held by Dhoni!
tossed up from around the stumps, pitches and spins in, he's made room to leg and cuts to cover
tossed up down leg stump, he turns it away in the air Dhoni moves around to field
identical delivery, this time he nudges it to Yuvraj at short fine leg
quicker one, he comes out and drives to Karthik at midwicket
tossed up, this time he gets further out and hammers it over midwicket, out to the fielder on one bounce in the deep
tossed up too wide, and he gets off the mark with a slash through the covers
tossed up on a length, he gets forward and defends
tossed up on off stump, gets a step forward and tickles it to short fine leg for one
tossed up outside off stump, comes in as Hall gets forward and defends to point
quicker arm ball, just enough room for him to cut hard to backward point
tossed up on middle and off, flicked into the midwicket region and the bowler does the fielding
tossed up outside off stump, he gets forward and drops the hands on it, point does the fielding
tossed up on a good length, he backs away and drives to point
tossed up outside off stump, he clears the front leg and clouts this over midwicket
tossed up on middle and leg, nicely worked in front of square leg
tossed up on middle and leg, he shuffles across and taps it fine for one
a touch full and flat, Boucher uses the feet and clips out to the fielder
tossed up just outside off stump, Hall gets across and as the ball spins in he has to defend off the back foot
tossed up outside off stump, Boucher sweeps out to Tendulkar at deep midwicket

tossed up, he comes forward and defends, the ball rolls away and Boucher calls for one, there's some stumbling, both men stranded, then they decide what the hell, lets run, and Hall is let off by a poor collection from Yuvraj
tossed up, he comes out and drives to mid-off for one
back of a length outside off stump, he cuts to cover
short and wide, he stands and cuts but misses
tossed up, he drives to Ganguly at mid-off
flat outside off stump, cut for one
flat on the stumps, pulled through midwicket and a fumble from Zaheer allows the second
good heave, coming out, making room, and clubbing this one over mid-on for half a dozen!
moves around the stumps, flights up a full toss that Boucher cant put away with his slog sweep
tossed up, he backs away to leg, isnt to the pitch, beaten in the flight, but gets enough bat on it to clear extra cover
flat outside leg stump, he tries to pull but misses
tossed up, kicks off the seam and beats his backfoot shot
tossed up, short of a length, hit to long-off for a single
shortish ball on the stumps, Boucher comes out and hits it on the up to Powar at long-on
tossed up, he comes out and drives to long-off
tossed up, he clears the front leg and swipes out to Tendulkar in the deep
steps out, the ball's fired in short and quick, he hits it to mid-on, where another poor throw gets them overthrows
too full on leg stump, turned out to Ganguly at fine leg
slow and full outside off stump, gets down on one knee and drives to mid-off for one
good ball, attempted yorker in the zone but Hall does well to flick it from leg stump, wide of fine leg for four
full outside off stump, driven to long-off
yorker ends up full toss on the stumps, driven to long-on
comes out, the ball's short of a length, and he cant beat Dravid at midwicket
tossed up, uses the feet and clobbers it hard back over his head for four, good shot!
short on middle and leg, pulled out to wide long-on and he gets to his 50, well played
tossed up on the stumps, driven back down the ground
bowled! Short, flat, accurate on the stumps, he makes room to biff it away but misses
tossed up, he tries a short-arm jab but misses
tossed up outside off stump, he gets down and steers it to third man
full outside off stump, he gets down and swings it over mid-on, some good fielding in the deep from Karthik, with a good dive, keeps them to two
full outside off stump, hit back to Zaheer, who parries it off his followthrough, the ball rolls into the gap at cover but Boucher turns down the single
good stuff, full and no room to work with, he hits it back to Zaheer
dropped! Short of a length, he sweeps across the line and a hard, flat chance is spilled by Dravid, moving to his left at square leg
fullish on middle and leg, driven down to Ganguly at long-on
full and wide, he backs away and swings, getting a thick edge down to third man

inn2.comm: back of a length, angled across him of a short length, and he plays and misses
beaten! Another shortish delivery, on that virtually unplayable channel outside off stump, nipping off the seam and beating his back-foot defense
and again! Ganguly gets up and plays at one pushed across him, off the back foot, and misses the line totally
this one's short outside leg stump, and he gets India on the board with a deflected edge down to fine leg
short delivery on the stumps, comes in a good pace and surprises Tendulkar, hopping up and keeping it down in front of short leg with one hand
thats an excellent lifter outside off stump, forcing him up and then across
good length outside off stump, Ganguly gets up and plays at it, and manages to squeeze  it past a diving backward point
back of a length, seaming away outside off stump, and once more Ganguly fishes at it, misses, and then shakes his head in anger
good length on the stumps, he gets his head down and defends to point
back of a length, moving across the stumps with the angle, and now Ganguly leaves well
good length just outside off stump, and its defended back down the track
back of a length outside off stump, he does well to defend this gently down to backward point
good lifter outside off stump, Tendulkar holds back on the shot, allowing it to pass safely
back of a length, he shuffles across off stump and defends back to Ntini with a little "WAIT" back to Ganguly
back of a length, he again shuffles across to outside off stump and deflects it to leg, no chance of a run though
back of a length, going on with the wide angle past leg stump, Tendulkar shuffles across and shoulders arms, wide called
banged in short again, fourth ball in a row Tendulkar shuffles across, but this time he pulls behind square leg very well
back of a length on about off stump, up he gets, working the wrists on it but failing to beat square leg
good ball, beating the outside edge off another well-directed short delivery outside off stump, Tendulkar getting up and trying to defend
back of a length again to the left-hander, pushed across at a good pace and Ganguly leaves it alone
back of a length outside off stump, Ganguly plays it late with an open face of the bat and he finds the gap behind square for one to third man
overpitched on leg stump, bread n butter, no hassles flicking that through the gap at midwicket for four
short of a length outside off stump, and Tendulkar flirts with it, with minimal footwork
full on leg stump again, he gets up and rolls the wrists on the shot, square leg dives but its all in vain, four more to Tendulkar
good length outside off stump, looking for movement, but Tendulkar lets that one go
bouncer outside off stump, he ducks and lets it pass
oh ho! Ganguly's feet dont move as he feels for a short delivery outside off stump, the ball just passing by the face of the bat
back of a length again, this time he leaves it be
back of a length on the stumps, he gets up and defends it down in front of point
good ball! Another short-pitched delivery sits up and lures Ganguly up on the back foot, playing at that one and missing
and thats his way of countering this kind of bowling, backing away and freeing the arms to crack that through the covers
suh-weet! Just a bit of room offered and he times that beautifully off the back foot in front of point, firm cut shot
a little room on offer again and this is a better back-foot punch but it doesnt beat point
good length, rising delivery outside off stump, Tendulkar gets a good look at it and watches it into Boucher's mits
back of a length outside off stump, Tendulkar gets up and defends off the back foot with a firm "NO"
fullish on off stump, angling in, and he whips it to the square leg fielder
close! Tendulkar gets up in the crease, fending at one and the outside edge flies wide of Kallis second slip, who dives to his right but cant quite hold on
great delivery! Pitches on a good length and then straightens, beating him off the back foot
bang, thats four! Ntini pitches short, Tendulkar swivels, and the ball is pulled over square leg
and the response is a cracker, short and lifting outside off stump, forcing Tendulkar to drop the hands and get the head back
back of a length, coming on with the wide angle, and he defends it back down the track, getting up on the toes
immense! Tendulkar's taking Ntini on! Another attempted short delivery on the stumps disappears in a flash over square leg, landing a couple feet in front of the ropes
good length delivery coming in, he moves across before, premeditated, but cant work this one away, the ball dropping at his feet
overpitched, a touch slower, and Ganguly pushes it to cover
back of a length, he covers the line and defends it well to the off side
short and wide, rising, and he plays this uppishly over gully for one to third man
good length on the stumps, defended back towards midwicket
back of a length, he gets back and punches off the back foot, Duminy misfields and he gets one
short delivery, he too decides to pull, not timed well but he gets two through mid-on
good length delivery, Tendulkar doesnt get forward or back, and ends up pushing at it to get beaten
short delivery coming into him, he leans back and tries some sort of late cut but misses
another short delivery outside off stump, Tendulkar tries to pull but doesnt make contact
good length delivery comes in, he just nudges it to midwicket
short again outside off stump, and he tries to dab it over the slips, ball comfortably beating the bat, and third man licks his lips
good length delivery, angling down leg stump, he tries to turn it away but the inside-edge slips inside his left pad, he reaches in and throws it back to Ntini
back of a length outside off stump, steered down to third man off the back foot
a touch fuller outside off stump, and Tendulkar drives lazily to cover
full and moving in sharply off the seam, 140ks, Tendulkar gets the front pad in and leaves it, it comes very close to off stump and he smiles exchanged both ways
back of a length outside off stump, he plays and misses
good length outside off stump, he gets a stride in and shoulders arms
good length again, moving in from outside off, and Tendulkar shoulders arms
good length on the stumps, defended to cover
hammered! Ganguly comes down the track and carves this over off side for four
pitches outside leg stump, back of a length, cramps him for room this time
again he backs away to leg and comes down the pitch, but the balls not on for that shot and he has to defend it to cover
fuller outside leg stump, Ganguly shuffles across the stumps and taps that straight to square leg
good length, slower delivery on leg stump, and he works that to Duminy at square leg for a quick single this time
and Gunther does well, pitching this on a good length for Ganguly to defend
back of a length on middle and leg, catches Ganguly on the hop and strikes him high above the stumps, the ball rolls to point and they scamper one
back of a length outside off stump, defended well to point
no stopping that, as Tendulkar gets into position to cut a short delivery, off the back foot, through point
good length this time, drawing him forward in textbook defense
slower delivery, on a good length, and he punches to cover
fullish delivery on off stump, he drives back down the ground and gets an inside-edge onto the front leg
shorter this time and he cuts it to backward point
comes down, making room to carve over the off side, but that shots not on, and he has to chop it to cover
a bit of room out side off stump, he cuts into the ground, de Villiers at backward point misfields, and thats India's 50
good length on the stumps, defended back down the track
good length, pushed to cover off the back foot
back of a length outside off stump, steered down to third man
short of a length and he cuts off the back foot, de Villiers dives but cant stop that one
good length on the stumps, he shuffles and defends it back, was already expecting a short ball
back of a length, Ganguly runs that down to third man
much fuller outside off stump, he leaves it be
good length delivery outside off stump, defended to cover
overpitched outside off stump, from around the stumps, he drives loosely and gets an inside-edge to short fine leg
back of a length outside off stump, Tendulkar square-drives behind point and Nel dives well on the ropes to save runs
back of a length outside off stump, he gets up and defends to Gibbs at point
good length delivery, pitching outside off stump and swinging down leg, catches him in the crease but Hall doesnt appeal as he knows it was doing too much, the ball rolls towards gully
full and wide, he reaches out a good distance and drives this past a fumbling point and the outfield does the rest
good length on the stumps, driven back to Hall
good length outside off stump, Ganguly drives with zero footwork and gets beaten
a touch fuller outside off stump, he stands and pushes at it, getting an inside-edge down to Tshabalala at fine leg, Nel isnt amused at all
good short delivery on off stump, forcing Tendulkar up on the toes, and he keeps it down to the feet
a bit fuller this time, on off stump, as Tendulkar shuffles and drives to mid-on
good length on the stumps, he looks to work it fine but the ball stops on him and he has to adjust, with soft hands, to defend back a glaring Nel
back of a length outside off stump, he gets up and plays it, but misses
fullish on off stump, he shuffles and flicks down to Nel at fine leg
good length outside off stump, he gets half-forward and drives tamely to point, didnt time it well
shot! Tendulkar cashes in on the width, opening the face and steering that in the gap behind point for four more
a touch fuller on off stump, Tendulkar shuffles and rolls the wrists over it, its not timed perfectly but has enough on it to get him a couple more through midwicket
back of a length outside off stump, he gets up and taps it in front of square leg, telling Ganguly to hold his ground at the non-striker's end
slower delivery ends up sliding past Tendulkar's pads for a wide
overpitched, he drives well back to Hall, who fields it and throws it back to Tendulkar, who gets out of the way and the ball splays the stumps
back of a length, from around the stumps this time, and Ganguly defends to point with soft hands
good length delivery, defended with an inside-edge onto the back leg, Tendulkar wants the single and sprints through, Nel too hurdles down the pitch and tries to kick the ball onto the stumps
slower delivery, full too, and he unleashes an ambitious drive, connecting with nothing but air
awesome! Nel drops short outside off stump, and has to watch the ball sail over deep backward square leg for maximum! A powerful pull shot for six
follows up with a slower one, on a good length, and its crunched to cover

50! Tendulkar drives a good length delivery into the covers, sprints down the other end, the throw is awful and goes for four overthrows, and THAT, everyone, is 15,000 ODI runs for the man...take a bow
good length outside off stump, driven to de Villiers at cover off the back foot
slower delivery, good length outside off stump, he walks into it and defends back to Hall
short of a length angling down leg stump, he helps it on its way and Langeveldt does well to keep them to one
good length outside off stump, Ganguly gets behind the ball and defends off the back foot
comes down the track, drives on the up, and Tshabalala, standing at mid-off, doesnt pick it even as his team-mates shout "CATCH IT" and the ball evades him to his left
lifter outside off stump, he arches his back and goes for the uppercut, but doesnt  make contact, much to his frustration
back of a length outside off stump, he leaves it be
fuller delivery outside off stump, from around the stumps still, and Ganguly defends it back
bouncer over the stumps, he gets down and the umpire signals one for the over
back of a length, he defends off the back foot to cover
back of a length outside off stump, he gets up and steers it down to third man
comes forward and drives a good-length delivery on the up, mid-off fields in vain and thats another boundary to Tendulkar
good length outside leg stump, he tries to flick but doesnt time it all that well
back of a length going down he stump, he turns it to Langeveldt at short fine leg for one
now he walks well across the stumps as the ball comes out the bowler's hand, its angled down leg stump and sails dangerously over it
slower ball on off stump, he comes forward and turns it to Ntini at mid-on
back of a length outside off stump, gets back and steers it to Gibbs at backward point, who dives to his left and stops it, with a fumble
fuller delivery on about off stump, he drives straight to the man at mid-on
full outside leg stump, he works it to Duminy at square leg, one of five men on the leg side
slow down leg stump again, swept to Duminy
full on leg stump, this time he tucks it to midwicket, where de Villiers moves fast and forces Ganguly to turn back and dive into his crease
serves up a full toss, he comes down but cant put it away, hitting to mid-on
tossed up on leg stump, Ganguly comes forward and defends
tossed up on middle and leg, he gets well forward and defends
short delivery outside off stump, he goes for the pull, not timing it well at all and luckily for him it drops into no mans land near long-on
but thats timed to perfection! Tendulkar just walks into a free-flowing, textbook cover drive into the gap for four
short of a length, he stands up on the toes and tries to work it to leg, ends up with a leading edge that dies just before point
back of a length down leg stump, turned out to Langeveldt at fine leg for a single
slower delivery, back of a length outside off stump, he opens the face and gives Langeveldt more work to do, this time at third man
back of a length on off stump, he turns the bat and works one just to leg, calls for the single and thats India's 100 up
served up full and flat on off stump, and its whipped to a diving midwicket
comes out, the ball is fired down leg stump, fairly wide, Ganguly isnt to the pitch at all, but plays it superbly, with the spin, for six over mid-on
tossed up on off stump, he comes forward and defends
quicker delivery into leg stump, he advances again and mistimes the shot to midwicket
full and flat down leg stump, he sweeps well but straight to Duminy at short fine leg
again flat down leg stump, this time he doesnt time his attempted sweep well
back of a length on off stump, easily worked to square leg off the back foot
good length, angling outside off stump, left alone
angled a touch wider  this time, and now Ganguly tries to dab it down to third man but misses
comes down, making room to leg, flays the bat at it and picks up four over slip
overpitched, the slower one, well driven but a full-blooded dive at mid-off robs him of a boundary
back of a length outside off stump, steered to backward point
tossed up slower, he drives hard to mid-off
tossed up again, this time he steps out and drives harder, but Kallis dives very well at mid-off and fields it
tossed up even wider, and he square-drives to point
comes dancing down the track, Tshabalala bowls it wide, forcing him to play against the turn, over the top, and it lands safely in the deep for two
full and wide, he drives off the back foot to deep cover
from around the stumps, tossed up on middle and leg, Ganguly comes out and lifts this over mid-on and once again the ball drops safely in no mans land
good length on the stumps, he rolls the wrists and drives to mid-on
back of a length, played with soft hands to Gibbs at point
short of a length, he gets up and plays it down to the off side for a quick single
overpitched outside off stump, allowing him to drive through  the covers
back of a length on middle and leg, he shuffles and turns it to square leg
good length outside off stump, steered to Gibbs at point
tossed up outside leg stump, he tries to turn it away but the inside-edge rolls very close to leg stump
and there it is! He dances down and hammers this over long-on for half a dozen!
comes down, getting to the pitch and clubbing this down to long-off for four this time!
a flatter one this time on middle and leg, defended to the on side
flat down leg stump, he gets down on one knee and tries to sweep, but doesnt connect well at all
short and wide, he rocks back and cuts hard, the ball shoots right between Kallis' legs at cover, and Tendulkar has another four!
there's a wicket! Back of a length delivery, Ganguly comes out and reaches for the square-drive, but can only steer it into the safe hands of Gibbs at backward point!
good length delivery on the stumps, he gets up and defends it
a touch fuller, just, and Dravid gets forward to defends to cover
short of a length, gets up on him but he's upto the task, playing it with soft hands
back of a length outside off stump, played to backward point
overpitched outside off stump, he reaches out and drives, chopping into the ground before a diving de Villiers in the cover
tossed up, he drives to cover
tossed up outside off stump, turns and he gets an inside-edge to midwicket
short, flat and wide and he cuts hard through the covers out to sweeper
flat on leg stump, worked to midwicket for one
tossed up outside off stump, on a good length, he waits for it and then steers to point
a little quicker and fuller, drawing him forward and he drives to mid-off, hesitantly, for one
full on leg stump, he shuffles and turns that in the air wide of midwicket, runs hard but only gets one
back of a length outside off stump, he chops that straight to Gibbs at backward point
quicker delivery, on a good length, forcing Dravid to play and miss
back of a length on leg stump, tucked to Duminy at square leg for a quick single
short of a length outside off stump, he gets up and plays that down to third man

caught and bowled! Langeveldt drops one short, and gets it to come onto Dravid quickly, at a sharp height, and as he jumps up and tries to turn it to square leg the bat face closes and the resultant leading-edge is easily held by the bowler
tossed up gently outside off stump, and a watchful Tendulkar gets well forward to defend
tossed up on off stump, and again he gets well forward to present the bat
slower delivery on middle and off, turned to midwicket
gives it a lot of air this time, and he calmly turns it to the fielder again

bowled 'em! Having been kept quite for four deliveries, he makes room to dab a tossed-up delivery, but loses the plot as the ball turns in sharply and takes the inside-edge onto middle and off...Tendulkar falls in the 90s for the second consecutive match and yet again a rookie spinner has his number
thats a wide, down the leg side
tossed up, he comes forward and defends
back of a length on middle and leg, tucked away to backward square leg to get off the mark
back of a length outside off stump, he covers it and shoulders arms

cleaned up! Ntini strikes with a full delivery outside off stump, drawing Dhoni forward and producing a false shot, a poor attempt at a drive, the ball sneaks through the big bat-and-pad gap and thuds into the base of off stump
full outside off stump, he comes forward and shoulders arms
good length delivery, he defends it back
tossed up, defended back
tossed up outside off stump, he comes out and drives to cover
tossed up, defended
tossed up on middle and leg, he goes back and defends
short and wide, he cuts to point
tossed up, he comes forward and defends
good shot, coming forward to a full delivery and pushing back down past mid-on for four
good length outside off stump, left alone
good length again outside off stump and again Karthik shoulders arms
overpitched, he comes onto the front foot and drives straight to mid-off
short of a length, forcing him up on the toes and he defends it back
comes down the track, driving on the up over extra cover, losing one hand on the bat and the ball, not the first time this innings, drops in no mans land...whats Karthik thinking?
tossed up just outside off stump, he gets forward and defends
tossed up, Yuvraj uses the feet and hammers this over mid-on for four
tossed up wide, he cuts and gets a thick outside-edge down to third man, Ntini has work to do and does so well
tossed up outside off stump, he gets a big stride in and paddles this around the corner for two
tossed up, good flight and turn from Tshabalala, Karthik comes forward and defends
gives it some good air again, but Karthik dances out, gets to the pitch and drives in the gap at cover
good length outside off stump, steered down to third man for one
back of a length outside off stump, Yuvraj stands leaden-footed and flirts with it
marginally overpitched wide of off stump, Yuvraj leans forward and opens the face, steering to third man
bouncer down leg stump, wide called, Boucher fumbles and they steal a run, he then throws back a direct hit but Yuvraj is safe
good length on the stumps, defended to point where Gibbs fields
short of a length and Yuvraj chases it outside off stump, lucky not to get an edge
good length on off stump, he gets up and just drops it in front of cover, calling for the quick single and getting it
fullish delivery outside off stump, Yuvraj drops the bat on it, getting an inside-edge past a diving Boucher
fullish again, pushed past him and this time he leaves it alone
good length, poked off the back foot to Gibbs at backward point
overpitched just outside off stump, Yuvraj drives with a flourish to mid-off
good length, angled past him, and he steers this to a prowling Gibbs again
fractionally short, and he tries out the pull, hitting into the ground, that shot was not on
good length on the stumps, drawing him forward and he gets an inside-edge to leg
good length on leg stump, he cant beat the infield this time
back of a length outside off stump, chopped to that man Gibbs at backward point
halfvolley outside off stump, Yuvraj gets down and laces this out to deep cover
short-pitched delivery on the stumps, Karthik does well to get up and nudge it down to fine leg
good length outside off stump, Yuvraj pokes at it and gets beaten, Boucher oooh-aaahing behind the stumps as he collects
good length delivery outside off stump, Karthik lunges forward and drives, getting a thick outside-edge past a diving slip, third man fields
good length outside off stump, defended towards Gibbs, Yuvraj wants one but a smart Karthik says nothing doing, boss
good length on leg stump, he shuffles and attempts to work it away but mistimes the shot
a touch fuller this time, and Yuvraj gets forward to defend
short of a length outside off stump, he pulls hurriedly into the gap at square leg
full delivery outside off stump, he comes forward and drives to point
short of a length on middle and leg, he again gets across and tries to niggle it away but fails as the ball gains on  him
good length, he quickly comes forward and tries to push it past Gibbs, but cant
short of a length, he opens the face of the bat and steers that over slip, and a tumbling van Wyk at third man does very well
pacy, good length delivery draws him into his shot early, but he somehow manages to hold back on it, the ball dropping perilously close to de Villiers at cover
this one jags in off a length, and catches him square in the midriff as he shuffles up to defend, then scampers a single
lovely delivery to end the over, lifting sharply off a short length and beating Yuvraj all ends up
good length on middle and leg, pushed into the midwicket and they sprint a single
full and wide, cut out past point for one
good length on the stumps, defended back, good bowling
slower delivery, on a length, Karthik dangerously makes room and ends up running it coolly down to third man
full on off stump, he defends to Gibbs at backward point
good length, he plays with soft hands towards point, calls for one, de Villiers returns a loose throw that no one backs up and thet get a second
good one, taking off a from back of a length and Karthik is flummoxed by that one
good length, played with soft hands near the stumps and responding well to Yuvraj's call
wide delivery down leg stump, South Africa dont need that, though they've kept the extras to a bare minimum
good length outside off stump, Yuvraj square-drives off the front foot streakily and edges one down to third man
full on leg stump, he turns that over Gibbs at midwicket, a poor shot that lands safely
bouncer outside off stump, he flays the bat at it and then looks at the umpire
back of a length outside off stump, he drops the hands on it and runs it through gully
good length on the stumps, played gently into the covers, takes a few steps out and then sends Yuvraj, halfway down the track, back to his end but the throw doesnt come in well enough
drifts onto leg stump and he flicks it down to fine leg
good length on leg stump, worked to the fielder, no chance for a run
bouncer! Over middle stump, forcing Yuvraj down onto his haunches
good length outside off stump this time, Yuvraj stands grounded and flirts with it
a touch fuller this time, he gets forward and then holds back the shot, the ball pops up and lands agonizingly in between cover and point and Nel shakes his head

loosener, wide of off stump, giving Karthik room to steer it down to third man, running two, Boucher whips off the bails on the return, behind him, its referred upstairs but the green light comes on soon
steps across the stumps and tries to hit one down leg away for runs, but its a wide
a bit of room on offer and he cuts hard but that man Gibbs is electric at point, moving to his left and pouncing on it
short outside leg stump, he swivels on one leg and pulls down to fine leg for two
good length outside off stump, he stands and steers it down to Tshabalala at third man
back of a length outside off stump, he arches back and runs this neatly down to third man for another single
a bit fuller this time, Karthik comes onto the front foot and drives to cover
good length, just outside off stump, forcing him to play and miss, good ball at this time of the innings...in fact, at any time of the innings
fuller on the pads, Yuvraj clips through square out to Duminy in the deep
full outside off stump, Karthik punches towards mid-off, who's back deep, for one
pitches on leg stump, Yuvraj turns it straight to the man at midwicket
a touch too full on middle and leg and Yuvraj whips this, a rasping pick-up shot, over midwicket for four, the first boundary for seven overs
and the next delivery is a bouncer outside off stump, which Yuvraj lets go
good length on middle and leg, tucked into the gap at square leg and he gets one
slower delivery, fullish outside off stump, and he drives to short extra cover
short and wide, well steered down past backward point, on the second run Karthik slips but all is well
full and wide, he drives with poor footwork and misses
a touch wider, but the result  is the same as Yuvraj flashes and fails to connect
short outside leg stump, he gets up on one leg and turns this past short fine leg
full on leg stump, tucked out to backward square leg for one
full on middle and off, he whips this through square leg for a brace
makes room and drills a full delivery on off stump through point, but it yields just a single out to the man on boundary duty
makes room to leg and smashes a length delivery through the covers and Nel does well on the ropes to dive and keep them to a pair
wow! Yuvraj picks the full delivery outside leg stump excellently over deep backward square leg for a flat six
slower delivery on a length, he calmly pushes it to mid-off and calls for the single
good length delivery on off stump, moves away and he pushes to cover
good length on middle and leg, tucking him up as he tries to work it to midwicket, ends up pushing back to the bowler
makes room to leg stump again, cutting hard through point but finding the man back on the ropes
quick bouncer outside off stump, but he gets up and steers it through the vacant slip region for one
slower delivery, full on leg stump, Yuvraj loses control of the chip shot off the pads but he places it over the infield and down in front of the man at deep midwicket
well placed, Yuvraj leaning forward and steering a wide delivery through gully and beating third man's chase
wide delivery outside off stump, Karthik coolly places that past a diving gully and steals the winning runs as India level the Future Cup with one to play!
